                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1110 Wallace, Henry A./203: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-11T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 11, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>696. I have just returned from accompanying the Vice President on his 3–day tour
                    of Bolivia outside the Capital. Everywhere Mr. Wallace was received with genuine
                    enthusiasm. I believe that his trip to Bolivia was successful in every way.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Duggan at Lima.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
